{{- define "code-planner-tools" -}}

CODE PLANNER TOOLS:
- liza submit-for-review — Submit code plan for review
  liza submit-for-review {{.TaskID}} <SHA> --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
  Get SHA first: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD
- liza await-verdict — Block until review verdict arrives (call after submit-for-review; budget-aware)
  liza await-verdict {{.TaskID}} --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
- liza write-checkpoint — Write pre-execution checkpoint (REQUIRED before submission)
  liza write-checkpoint {{.TaskID}} --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --intent "<what>" --validation-plan "<how to verify>" --files-to-modify "<file1>" --json
- liza set-task-output — Persist structured task definitions for downstream task creation
  liza set-task-output {{.TaskID}} --output <path.json> --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
  Create <path.json> with a file-writing tool, not a Bash heredoc (heredoc with JSON triggers a shell safety block).
  JSON file contains: [
    {"desc": "...", "done_when": "...", "scope": "...", "spec_ref": "...", "plan_ref": "...", "depends_on": ["0", "2"]}
  ]
  depends_on: optional array of sibling index strings. "0" means "depends on output[0]".
  Indices are resolved to child task IDs at transition time.
- liza handoff — Context near exhaustion (~90%)
  liza handoff {{.TaskID}} "<what is done>" "<exact next step>" --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
- liza mark-blocked — Cannot proceed
  liza mark-blocked {{.TaskID}} --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --reason "<what is blocking>" --questions "<q1>" --questions "<q2>" --json
{{- end -}}
